Interface UsbDevice

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<UsbDevice>, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractUsbDevice, FreeBsdUsbDevice, LinuxUsbDevice, MacUsbDevice, SolarisUsbDevice, WindowsUsbDevice

    public interface UsbDevice
extends Serializable, Comparable<UsbDevice>
    A USB device is a device connected via a USB port, possibly internally/permanently. Hubs may contain ports to which other devices connect in a recursive fashion.
    Author:
    widdis[at]gmail[dot]com
